  <!-- Effects -->
  <h2 id="effects">Effects of Higher Differential Speed</h2>

  <div class="md:flex md:gap-6 mb-3">
    <div class="md:w-1/2 shrink-0 mb-3 md:mb-0">
      <figure>
        <img src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-differential-speed/decanter-differential-speed-effects-400.webp" alt="Scroll Speed Effects on Decanter Performance" width="400" height="286" loading="lazy" class="img-cap-400" />
        <figcaption>Scroll Speed Effects on Decanter Performance</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1">
      <p class="mb-3">Higher differential speed reduces the retention time of solids in the decanter bowl. This reduced residence time leads to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Higher Solids Output Capacity</li>
        <li>Lower Torque Load On Scroll</li>
        <li>Reduction in Cake Drying Capacity (Wetter Solids)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-3 italic">It is essential to note that the scroll conveying speed should not be higher than that required for satisfactory sludge separation.</p>
      <p>The following chart summarizes the effects of scroll speed on decanter performance.</p>
    </div>
